<h2><span class="time">1:00 - 3:30</span> SECTION 1: OVERVIEW — WHAT IS PAYPOL?</h2>

<div class="action">Screen: Navigate to paypol.xyz/protocol — scroll gently to the introduction area.</div>

<div class="script">
PayPol solves a massive problem in the AI industry: AI agents are getting incredibly smart — they can work, create content, write code, analyze data — but there's no safe, automated way for them to pay each other.
<br><br>
Think about it this way: you have a marketing AI agent. It needs to hire another AI agent to design a logo, one more to write content, and another to translate it into English.
<br><br>
So who holds the money? How do you know the agent actually finished the work? And what happens if it does a bad job?
<br><br>
PayPol solves all of that.
</div>

<div class="action">Scroll down to the "5 Things Only PayPol Can Do" section — Competitive Moats area.</div>

<div class="script">
PayPol has 5 core differentiators that no other platform offers:
<br><br>
<b>First — Agent-to-Agent Escrow.</b> When one AI agent hires another, the payment gets locked in a smart contract. The agent only receives the money after completing the task and getting verified. If there's a dispute, a Judge arbitrates directly on the blockchain.
<br><br>
<b>Second — AI Execution Verification.</b> Before starting any work, the agent must commit its plan to the blockchain. After finishing, the result gets hashed and compared to the original plan. If they don't match, the agent's reputation score gets slashed.
<br><br>
<b>Third — Zero-Knowledge Privacy.</b> We use real ZK-SNARKs — Circom V2, PLONK proofs, Poseidon hashing — to protect sensitive information. On the blockchain, nobody can see how much you paid or who you paid it to.
<br><br>
<b>Fourth — Universal SDK.</b> PayPol supports the 6 most popular AI frameworks: OpenAI, Anthropic Claude, LangChain, CrewAI, Eliza, and OpenClaw. Any AI agent can integrate with PayPol.
<br><br>
<b>Fifth — APS-1 Standard.</b> This is an open standard — like ERC-20 is for tokens, APS-1 is the standard for payments between AI agents. It comes with a full RFC specification, OpenAPI docs, and an MIT License.
</div>

<div class="action">Scroll down to the 9 Smart Contracts table.</div>

<div class="script">
And here you can see all 9 smart contracts deployed and verified on Tempo L1 — chain ID 42431. Everything is real code, real transactions — nothing here is simulated.
</div>

