Click "View ZK Proof" to see details: deposit transaction, payout transaction, and status of each recipient. Everything is a real on-chain transaction.
</div>

<div class="action">Click on a batch — expand the breakdown detail.</div>

<div class="script">
When expanded, you can see each recipient: name, wallet address, amount, and a direct link to the on-chain transaction. Every payment can be independently verified on the block explorer.
</div>

<h3><span class="time">9:00 - 10:00</span> 3D: Shield Mode — ZK-SNARK Privacy</h3>

<div class="action">Toggle Shield mode ON in the OmniTerminal.</div>

<div class="script">
Now I'm turning on Shield mode — this is PayPol's highest-security feature, powered by ZK-SNARKs.
</div>

<div class="action">Type: "Pay 1000 AlphaUSD to 0xABCD... with ZK privacy"</div>

<div class="script">
With Shield enabled, the transaction is processed through the ShieldVaultV2 smart contract. Behind the scenes, the system performs four steps:
<br><br>
One — generates a Zero-Knowledge proof using Circom V2 and snarkjs.
<br>
Two — hashes the recipient address and amount using Poseidon hashing.
<br>
Three — creates a nullifier to prevent double-spending.
<br>
Four — submits the proof to PlonkVerifierV2 for on-chain verification.
</div>

<div class="action">Show loading animation — proof being generated.</div>

<div class="script">
The proof is being generated right now... This is a real ZK-SNARK PLONK proof, not a simulation. Our daemon has been optimized with a Poseidon singleton cache. The first proof takes about 3 seconds, but subsequent proofs take less than a second thanks to caching.
</div>

<div class="action">Show success — transaction hash appears.</div>

<div class="script">
Done! The transaction is now on the blockchain. And here's the key point: on-chain, nobody can tell who the recipient is or what the amount was. Only the sender and receiver know — exactly as designed.
</div>

