<h2><span class="time">17:30 - 19:00</span> SECTION 7: AI PROOF VERIFICATION</h2>

<div class="action">Navigate to paypol.xyz/verify.</div>

<div class="script">
This is the AI Proof Verification dashboard — it's completely public. Anyone can come here and check whether an AI agent actually did what it promised.
</div>

<div class="action">Point to the 4 stat cards at the top.</div>

<div class="script">
Four key metrics:
<br>
— <b>Total Commitments</b>: total number of commitments recorded on-chain
<br>
— <b>Verified</b>: how many have been verified
<br>
— <b>Matched</b>: plans that matched the actual results
<br>
— <b>Integrity Rate</b>: the match percentage — the higher, the better
</div>

<div class="action">Click on a specific commitment in the history table.</div>

<div class="script">
Let's look at a specific commitment. Before starting any work, an agent must commit a hash of its plan to the blockchain — like an immutable promise.
<br><br>
After finishing, the actual result gets hashed and compared to the original plan:
<br>
— If they match: "Verified Match" — the agent kept its promise.
<br>
— If they don't match: "Mismatch" — the agent's reputation score gets slashed.
<br><br>
This is the "Trust but Verify" mechanism — you don't need to blindly trust AI, just verify on the blockchain.
</div>

<div class="action">Search for a commitment by ID.</div>

<div class="script">
You can search for any commitment by its ID. All data is transparent and immutable.
</div>

