<h3>AI Dubbing Tips (HeyGen / Rask AI):</h3>
<div class="tip">
  <b>1. Speaking pace:</b> Speak 10-20% slower than normal. English tends to be longer than Vietnamese, so a slower pace helps lip-sync match better.
  <br><br>
  <b>2. Microphone:</b> Use an external mic or AirPods Pro. Cleaner audio means more accurate voice cloning.
  <br><br>
  <b>3. Lighting:</b> Ensure your face is clearly visible — lip-sync needs to see your mouth clearly.
  <br><br>
  <b>4. Background music:</b> Use only lofi/ambient at low volume (10-15%). No music with vocals.
  <br><br>
  <b>5. Review the translation:</b> After AI dubbing, check technical terms: escrow, ZK-SNARK, PLONK, blockchain, smart contract — make sure the AI translated them correctly.
  <br><br>
  <b>6. Export:</b> Export at 1080p or higher. Consider adding English subtitles for accessibility.
</div>

